Step 1: Calculate the Free Cash Flow (FCF).  
• From the cash flow statement, FCF is computed as:  
  FCF = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities – Capital Expenditures  
• Here, the Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities is 116257.19 and the Purchase of Fixed Assets is 0.00.  
  FCF = 116257.19 – 0.00 = 116257.19  

Step 2: Calculate the Current Assets Turnover Ratio.  
• This ratio is defined as:  
  Current Assets Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue / Average Current Assets  
• Total Revenue (from the income statement) is 3025437.82.  
• The average current assets are calculated using the beginning current assets from 2023-12-31 and ending current assets from 2024-02-05:  
  Average Current Assets = (8000000.00 + 10022038.12) / 2  
  Average Current Assets = 18022038.12 / 2 = 9011019.06  
• Therefore, the ratio is:  
  Current Assets Turnover Ratio = 3025437.82 / 9011019.06 ≈ 0.3358, which rounds to 0.34  

Thus, the solution is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Free Cash Flow (FCF)": "116257.19",
    "Current Assets Turnover Ratio": "0.34"
  }
}
